country.name: Austria
country.overview: Austria is a German-speaking country in Central Europe, characterized by mountain villages, baroque architecture, Imperial history and rugged Alpine terrain. Vienna, its Danube River capital, is home to the Schönbrunn and Hofburg palaces. It has counted Mozart, Strauss and Freud among its residents. The country’s other notable regions include the northern Bohemian Forest, Traunsee Lake and eastern hillside vineyards.

geography.location_description: Central Europe, north of Italy and Slovenia
geography.area_note: about the size of South Carolina; slightly more than two-thirds the size of Pennsylvania
geography.climate: temperate; continental, cloudy; cold winters with frequent rain and some snow in lowlands and snow in mountains; moderate summers with occasional showers
geography.terrain: mostly mountains (Alps) in the west and south; mostly flat or gently sloping along the eastern and northern margins
geography.notes: landlocked; strategic location at the crossroads of central Europe with many easily traversable Alpine passes and valleys; major river is the Danube; population is concentrated on eastern lowlands because of steep slopes, poor soils, and low temperatures elsewhere
